@marty: I'm on your side - we want a real "copy of original structure" where Inbox is in same place like before (behind/under) new date folder. This is effectively on large archive interval like every year as in my case. This would be a "complete" Backup including all original folders/files in this time frame.


But I think I understand Ryan now.

@Ryan Rubley:How often do you want to archive? Do you have other folders beside Inbox on your mail account? Are "Send"-folder inside or beside your infox-folder? In #21 you write inbox is your root folder - but in my case it's not. Different provider handle this different. :-(

My main problem is that only inbox folder will be archived current, but my send folder is beside (not inside) inbox. So only received files are archive, but send files are missing.

